  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Increase case detection by 14000 cases from 3800 TB cases reported in 2013/14 (all forms of TB) by 2020Maintain the treatment success rate at 90% patients (all forms of TB) by 2020Provide MDR diagnostic services for 55% of persons with suspected MDR TB by 2017 and 100% by 2020; successfully treat at least 75 % of the diagnosed MDR patientsEngage 60% of all private health care providers (hospitals and practitioners) in TB control by 2017, and 80% by 2020Strengthen community systems for management, advocacy, support and rights for TB patients in order to create an enabling environment  to detect & manage TB cases in 60% of all districts by 2017 and 100% by 2020Ensure availability of quality TB services, in line with current international standards and provided by qualified personnel, at 70% of all facilities by 2017 and 90% of the facilities by 2020"
    },
